  "name": "2 Timothy 3:1–4:5",
  "localizedName": "2 Timothy 3:1–4:5",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108536",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "last days"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " people will treat each other badly. They will act the opposite of how Jesus taught "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108202",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "human beings"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " to live. They will follow their own desires instead of being controlled by God’s Spirit. They will teach lies about God. Certain people will try to trick others on purpose."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Timothy must stay away from people like that. Instead, he should follow Paul’s example. Paul was full of faith and love. He was patient and didn’t give up. He trusted in God to save him when he was treated badly. Timothy must also continue to be patient and careful as he taught about Jesus."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Paul called the good news about Jesus the Word. The message about Jesus is made clear in "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108200",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "God’s word"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Paul explained that God had breathed life into all Scripture. Breathing life into something is also what God did when he created human beings in Genesis 2:7. Paul meant that the Bible is more than a collection of words that humans wrote. God’s Spirit can use Scripture to teach believers and to heal wounds in their "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108419",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "heart"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Studying Scripture can train believers to do the good works God wants them to do."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Paul warned Timothy that he would be treated badly if he followed Jesus faithfully. People wouldn’t want to hear the message of truth. But he must keep doing the work God had given him."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
